From d8161ebca202a204abdd5f38333509b0689b6647 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 04:19:24 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: address round-2 review findings (regressions + gaps from
 latest push)

1. Revert src/middleware.ts back to src/proxy.ts (and the exported
   function name). Next.js 16.2.7 explicitly warns that the middleware
   file convention is deprecated and to use proxy instead - the rename
   went the wrong direction. Confirmed via a local build that this
   warning fires on middleware.ts and would not fire on proxy.ts.

2. Fix src/app/api/admin/series/[id]/route.ts PUT: now validates the
   body with updateSeriesApiSchema (already defined in lib/schemas.ts
   but never imported anywhere) via validateBody, matching the pattern
   already used correctly in movies/[id] and tags/[id]. Kept the
   validateSlug format check on top since zod's schema only checks
   min length, not the actual slug character format - verified against
   the create route (series/route.ts POST) which does both checks the
   same way.

3. Fix .gitignore: the old file's last line (*.csv) had no trailing
   newline, so the __pycache__ entry appended in the last commit got
   concatenated onto it, matching neither pattern. Split into separate
   lines and untracked the 4 .pyc files that were already committed -
   adding a pattern to .gitignore doesn't retroactively untrack files
   already in the repo.

4. Migrate the 8 non-admin routes that still hand-rolled the same
   session-check block withAuth was built to eliminate (8 of 16
   applicable routes had already been migrated, these are the other 8):
   movies/route.ts, movies/[slug]/route.ts, movies/[slug]/report,
   movies/[slug]/related, movies/[slug]/comments (GET+POST),
   upload/avatar, requests, favorites/toggle.
   - Passed each route's original error string as withAuth's new
     errorMessage param so response bodies are unchanged.
   - movies/[slug]/related keeps its own inner try/catch since it
     degrades to an empty related list on error instead of a 500 - that
     shape differs from the wrapper's generic error response, so it has
     to stay local to the handler.
   - upload/avatar previously returned the raw error message to the
     client on failure; it now returns a fixed generic message from the
     wrapper instead. Deliberate small behavior change (avoids leaking
     internal error text, e.g. a missing env var name, to the client) -
     flagging explicitly since it's not purely mechanical like the rest
     of this commit.
   Zero hand-rolled session-check blocks remain in src/app/api.

5. Fix components/entity-dialog.tsx: thumbnail/backdrop uploadKey was
   hardcoded to a movies-prefixed path regardless of which entity was
   being edited, so SeriesDialog (which renders through this same
   shared component) was filing series assets under the movies folder.
   Added an assetFolder prop; MovieDialog passes "movies", SeriesDialog
   passes "series".

6. Fix lib/admin-list.ts: multi-column search conditions were pushed
   into the same AND group as the column filters, so passing more than
   one search column would require the search term in ALL of them
   instead of matching if ANY contained it. No current caller passes
   more than one searchColumn so this hadn't surfaced yet, but it's
   exactly the kind of thing that silently breaks the first time
   someone extends it. Search conditions are now OR'd together before
   being AND-ed with the column filters.

7. Add the same errorMessage param to withAdminAuth that withAuth
   already had, for consistency between the two wrappers.

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, eslint clean (0 problems), grep-confirmed
zero remaining getCachedSession call sites outside lib/with-auth.ts and
lib/session.ts, zero remaining hand-rolled session-check blocks.
